goTips1: Shilling is a common practice in cryptocurrency where people tend to advertise the coins that they own in hopes of positively affecting the price. Quite often, it can be difficult to distinguish the difference between a shill or an unbiased post.
goTips2: When purchasing any cryptocurrency, it is advised to make the decision on your own before investing, and not just because someone else has said it is worth it.
is_honeypot0: This does not appear to be a honeypot
is_honeypotTips: If the contract is a honeypot, it will contain malicious code
is_open_sourceTips: If this token contract is open source. You can check the contract code for details. Unsourced token contracts are likely to have malicious functions to defraud their users of their assets
is_proxy0: Doesn't look like a proxy contract
is_proxyTips: The proxy contract means contract owner can modifiy the function of the token and possibly effect the price
owner_change_balance0: Owner can not tamper with balance
owner_change_balanceTips: In some contracts, the contract owner have the authority to modify the balance of tokens at other addresses
slippage_modifiableTips: If the tax can be modified, when the transaction tax is increased to more than 49%, the tokens will not be able to be traded (honeypot risk)
is_whitelistedTips: If there is a whitelist, some addresses may not be able to trade normally (honeypot risk)
is_blacklistedTips: If the blacklist function is included. Some addresses may not be able to trade normally (honeypot risk)
is_mintableTips: The contract may include additional issuing functions, which may generate a large number of tokens and affect the token price
can_take_back_ownershipTips: If this function exists, it is possible for the project owner to regain ownership even after relinquishing it
hidden_owner0: There doesn't appear to be a hidden owner
hidden_ownerTips: For contract with a hidden owner, developer can still manipulate the contract even if the ownership has been abandoned
selfdestructTips: If the contract has a self-destruct function and is triggered, the contract will be destroyed, all functions will be unavailable, and the related assets will be cleared
external_callTips: External contract invocations cause token contracts to be highly dependent on other contracts, which can be a potential risk
cannot_buyTips: If the token does not support purchase, then the token is typically issued as a reward for the on-chain app and cannot be purchased directly by the user
transfer_pausable0: No codes found to suspend trading
transfer_pausableTips: If a suspendable code is included, the token maybe neither be bought nor sold (honeypot risk)
is_in_dex1: This token can be traded on the main Dex
is_in_dex0: This token can not be traded on the main Dex
is_in_dexTips: If the token can be traded on a decentralized exchange, then we will provide the relevant transaction link
cannot_sell_all1: You can't sell all the tokens
cannot_sell_all0: All the tokens can be sold
cannot_sell_allTips: Some token contracts will have a maximum selling ratio (e.g., Sell up to 90% of your holdings)
is_anti_whaleTips: If there has limit to the number of token transactions, it is could be a scam token (honeypot risk)
anti_whale_modifiable0: Anti whale can not be modified
anti_whale_modifiableTips: If the trading maximum or the maximum open position can be modified, then the token contract is anti-whale
trading_cooldownTips: If there is a trading cooldown function, the user will not be able to sell the token within a certain time or block after buying
personal_slippage_modifiable1: Has tax changes found for personal addresses
personal_slippage_modifiable0: No tax changes found for personal addresses
